other awesome things like Startup Weekend or Random Hacks of
Kindness).

FRIDAY.

THIS FRIDAY.

DECEMBER ELEVENTH.

ON FRIDAY:
9pm: Arrive
10pm: Key signing party!
-> learn more about public key infrastructure from a talk by
Mike Franklin
12am: Facebook APIs!
-> learn how to use Facebook's wealth of data in your
application
morning: Go to sleep! [at your home]

Come to code! Come to learn! Come to talk to others that like
coding too! All night long! Food, energy, soda, power, fruit, and
snacks are provided!

C@N[7]

2011-04-20 18:24:19 -0400

The 7th Princeton ACM Code@Night was on 4/15. Prefrosh came!

We provided food, liquids, caffeine, snacks, chairs, tables, heating, bathrooms, air, doors, couches, and outlets.

This episode of C@N had a theme of:
NETWORK SECURITY!

At 11 pm, Hao Lian presented his talk on Dan Kaminsky's 2008 DNS cache poisoning attack.

Sponsored by USG. Who likes us. And gave us money. To get you food. So you can code. And be happy.
